{"slideshow_credits": null, "snippet": "Complex and controversial, the regulatory change allows businesses to advertise their offerings online, giving fans a chance to buy shares.", "abstract": "Regulatory shift involving rule known as Regulation A will allow smaller companies to raise up to $50 million by selling equity shares to investors of more modest means; change is intended to give companies an alternative to venture capital even if they have not yet had, or never plan on having, an initial public offering; practice has come to be referred to as 'mini IPOs'", "section_name": "Business Day", "print_page": "3", "document_type": "article", "byline": {"person": [{"firstname": "Stacy", "role": "reported", "lastname": "COWLEY", "rank": 1, "organization": ""}], "original": "By STACY COWLEY"}, "web_url": "http://www.nytimes.com/2015/06/19/business/smallbusiness/new-rules-let-companies-sell-stakes-to-investors-of-modest-means.html", "lead_paragraph": "Complex and controversial, the regulatory change allows businesses to advertise their offerings online, giving fans a chance to buy shares.", "headline": {"main": "New Rules Let Companies Sell Stakes to Investors of Modest Means", "print_headline": "&#8216;Mini I.P.O.s&#8217; Expand Pool of New Investors "}, "_id": "558334eb38f0d85931d0d4c8", "word_count": "1148", "multimedia": [{"height": 126, "url": "images/2015/06/19/business/19funding-web/19funding-web-thumbWide.jpg", "legacy": {"wideheight": "126", "wide": "images/2015/06/19/business/19funding-web/19funding-web-thumbWide.jpg", "widewidth": "190"}, "subtype": "wide", "width": 190, "type": "image"}, {"height": 400, "url": "images/2015/06/19/business/19funding-web/19funding-web-articleLarge.jpg", "legacy": {"xlarge": "images/2015/06/19/business/19funding-web/19funding-web-articleLarge.jpg", "xlargewidth": "600", "xlargeheight": "400"}, "subtype": "xlarge", "width": 600, "type": "image"}, {"height": 75, "url": "images/2015/06/19/business/19funding-web/19funding-web-thum